<taxonomicName authority="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera, 2020" authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2020" box="[617,857,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[617,857,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Bubaces occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[867,967,909,935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[867,961,909,935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
is included in the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1200,1310,910,935]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1310,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” group by having the total length of the body greater than 
<quantity box="[687,791,945,971]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.70 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2020" box="[801,1039,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[801,1039,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Bubaces occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is further segregated by having the dorsal surfaces of the pronotum, clavi and coria clothed with long hairs, the coria lacking circular yellow to creamy yellow subapical spots, and its distribution being restricted to the western parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1195,1017,1043]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1385,1018,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1385,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">B. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the surfaces of the pronotum, clavi and coria are glabrous, the coria also lack circular yellow to creamy yellow subapical spots, but its has a wide distribution, occurring from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[891,977,1089,1115]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(States of 
<collectingRegion box="[1099,1220,1089,1115]" country="Mexico" name="Campeche" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Campeche</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1231,1389,1089,1115]" country="Mexico" name="Quintana Roo" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Quintana Roo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,243,1125,1151]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="9" pageNumber="253">Yucatan</collectingRegion>
) throughout Central and South America.
</paragraph>
